{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":811,"text":"Why do people deliberately\ndestroy cultural heritage?"},{"time":6389,"text":"By doing so,"},{"time":7725,"text":"do they believe\nthey're erasing our history?"},{"time":11343,"text":"Our cultural memory?"},{"time":14570,"text":"It's true that we are losing\ncultural heritage to erosion"},{"time":19271,"text":"and natural disasters,"},{"time":21104,"text":"but this is something\nthat is simply difficult to avoid."},{"time":24876,"text":"I'm here to show you today\nhow we can use pictures --"},{"time":29006,"text":"your pictures --"},{"time":30888,"text":"to reclaim the history that is being lost"},{"time":34032,"text":"using innovative technology"},{"time":36279,"text":"and the effort of volunteers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40182,"text":"In the early 20th century,"},{"time":42227,"text":"archaeologists discovered\nhundreds of statues and artifacts"},{"time":46239,"text":"at the ancient city of Hatra,"},{"time":47997,"text":"in northern Iraq."},{"time":49976,"text":"Statues like this one\nwere found in fragments,"},{"time":53781,"text":"some of them missing their heads or arms,"},{"time":56942,"text":"yet the clothing that they are wearing"},{"time":59479,"text":"and their pose"},{"time":60949,"text":"can still tell us their story."},{"time":64239,"text":"For example,"},{"time":65413,"text":"we believe that by wearing\na knee-length tunic"},{"time":69171,"text":"and open bare feet,"},{"time":70695,"text":"this was representative of a priest."},{"time":73962,"text":"However, with a closer look\nat this particular piece,"},{"time":77807,"text":"we can see that this tunic being worn\nwas elaborately decorated,"},{"time":82253,"text":"which has led many researchers to believe"},{"time":85099,"text":"this was actually a statue of a king\nperforming his religious functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91126,"text":"When the Mosul Cultural Museum\nopened in 1952 in northern Iraq,"},{"time":97221,"text":"this statue, as well as others,"},{"time":99492,"text":"were placed there to preserve them\nfor future generations."},{"time":104265,"text":"Following the US-led invasion\nof Iraq in 2003,"},{"time":108228,"text":"a few statues and artifacts\nwere relocated to Baghdad,"},{"time":112117,"text":"but this statue remained."},{"time":115446,"text":"Then in February of last year,\na video was released,"},{"time":119230,"text":"and it instantly went viral."},{"time":122075,"text":"Maybe some of you remember seeing it."},{"time":124370,"text":"Here's a short clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125927,"text":"(Video) (Singing in Arabic)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151573,"text":"(Singing ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154107,"text":"Not a very pleasant sight, right?"},{"time":157679,"text":"Did you notice anything\nfamiliar in the video?"},{"time":161552,"text":"There it is."},{"time":163079,"text":"There is that very statue,"},{"time":165775,"text":"as it was toppled over,"},{"time":167542,"text":"breaking into pieces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169976,"text":"When Matthew Vincent and I saw this video,"},{"time":172861,"text":"we were shocked."},{"time":175059,"text":"Since we are archaeologists\nusing innovative technology"},{"time":178511,"text":"for digital preservation,"},{"time":180325,"text":"an idea sprung to mind."},{"time":182502,"text":"Maybe we can crowdsource the images\nthat were taken of these artifacts"},{"time":187339,"text":"before they were destroyed,"},{"time":189178,"text":"to create digital reconstructions."},{"time":191765,"text":"If we can do that,"},{"time":192939,"text":"maybe we can put them\ninto a virtual museum"},{"time":195054,"text":"to tell that story."},{"time":200030,"text":"And so two weeks after we saw this video,"},{"time":203558,"text":"we started the project\ncalled Project Mosul."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208328,"text":"Remember the pictures of the statue\nI showed you before?"},{"time":211471,"text":"This is actually the crowdsourced\nreconstruction of it"},{"time":215872,"text":"before it was destroyed."},{"time":218776,"text":"Now, many of you may be wondering,"},{"time":220923,"text":"how exactly does this work?"},{"time":222966,"text":"Well, the key to this technology\nis called photogrammetry,"},{"time":226365,"text":"and it was invented here, in Germany."},{"time":229890,"text":"It is the technology that allows us\nto use two-dimensional images"},{"time":233320,"text":"taken of the same object\nfrom different angles"},{"time":236293,"text":"to create a 3D model."},{"time":239269,"text":"I know you may be thinking\nthis sounds like magic -- but it's not."},{"time":243492,"text":"Let me show you how it works."},{"time":245047,"text":"Here are two crowdsourced images\nof the same statue."},{"time":248928,"text":"What the computer can do"},{"time":250347,"text":"is it can detect similar features\nbetween the photographs --"},{"time":254586,"text":"similar features of the object."},{"time":257569,"text":"Then, by using multiple photos,"},{"time":260569,"text":"in this case, it can begin\nto reconstruct the object in 3D."},{"time":264815,"text":"In this case,"},{"time":265989,"text":"you have the position of the cameras\nwhen each image was taken,"},{"time":269445,"text":"shown in blue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272282,"text":"Now, this is a partial\nreconstruction, I admit,"},{"time":275720,"text":"but why would I say partial?"},{"time":277617,"text":"Well, simply because the statue\nwas positioned against a wall."},{"time":282871,"text":"We don't have photographs\ntaken of it from the back."},{"time":286339,"text":"If I wanted to complete a full\ndigital reconstruction of this statue,"},{"time":291315,"text":"I would need a proper camera,"},{"time":293048,"text":"tripods, proper lighting,"},{"time":294817,"text":"but we simply can't do that\nwith crowdsourced images."},{"time":298149,"text":"Think about it:"},{"time":299323,"text":"How many of you, when you visit a museum,"},{"time":301580,"text":"take photographs\nof all parts of the statue,"},{"time":303845,"text":"even the back side of it?"},{"time":306406,"text":"Well, maybe if some of you find\nMichelangelo's David interesting,"},{"time":310027,"text":"I guess --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311202,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313168,"text":"But the thing is,"},{"time":314681,"text":"if we can find more images of this object,"},{"time":317845,"text":"we can improve the 3D model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321133,"text":"When we started the project,"},{"time":323331,"text":"we started it with\nthe Mosul Museum in mind."},{"time":325504,"text":"We figured we may get a few images,"},{"time":327195,"text":"some people interested,"},{"time":328465,"text":"make one or two virtual reconstructions,"},{"time":330968,"text":"but we had no idea that we had sparked\nsomething that would grow so quickly."},{"time":336276,"text":"Before we knew it,"},{"time":337853,"text":"we realized it was obvious:"},{"time":339908,"text":"we could apply this same idea\nto lost heritage anywhere."},{"time":344559,"text":"And so, we decided to change\nthe name of the project to Rekrei."},{"time":350007,"text":"Then, in the summer of last year,"},{"time":352551,"text":"\"The Economist\" magazine's media lab\nreached out to us."},{"time":356673,"text":"They asked us,"},{"time":357871,"text":"\"Hey, would you like us\nto build a virtual museum"},{"time":360662,"text":"to put the reconstructions back inside,"},{"time":362551,"text":"to tell the story?\""},{"time":364198,"text":"Can you imagine us saying no?"},{"time":365992,"text":"Of course not."},{"time":367317,"text":"We said yes!"},{"time":368492,"text":"We were so excited."},{"time":369673,"text":"This was exactly\nthe initial dream of that project."},{"time":373662,"text":"And so now,"},{"time":374873,"text":"any of you can experience\nRecoVR Mosul on your phone,"},{"time":378511,"text":"using Google Cardboard"},{"time":379828,"text":"or a tablet or even YouTube 360."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383044,"text":"Here is a screenshot\nfrom the virtual museum."},{"time":386524,"text":"And there it is ..."},{"time":388311,"text":"the partial reconstruction of the statue,"},{"time":390833,"text":"as well as the Lion of Mosul,"},{"time":393724,"text":"the first reconstruction\ncompleted by our project."},{"time":397539,"text":"Although the video doesn't explicitly show\nthe Lion of Mosul being destroyed,"},{"time":402353,"text":"we have many other examples\nof large artifacts being destroyed"},{"time":406510,"text":"that were simply too large\nto have been stolen."},{"time":410172,"text":"For example,"},{"time":411559,"text":"the Gate of Nimrud in northern Iraq."},{"time":414657,"text":"This is a digital\nreconstruction from before,"},{"time":417540,"text":"and this is actually\nduring the destruction."},{"time":421406,"text":"Or the Lion of Al-LƒÅt, in Palmyra, Syria:"},{"time":425050,"text":"before ..."},{"time":426901,"text":"and after."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429546,"text":"Although virtual reconstructions\nare primarily the main focus"},{"time":432840,"text":"of our project,"},{"time":434046,"text":"some people have been asking the question:"},{"time":436534,"text":"Can we print them in 3D?"},{"time":440555,"text":"We believe 3D printing\ndoesn't offer a straightforward solution"},{"time":444836,"text":"to lost heritage."},{"time":446338,"text":"Once an object is destroyed,"},{"time":448311,"text":"it's gone."},{"time":450052,"text":"But 3D printing does offer\nan addition to tell that story."},{"time":455739,"text":"For example, I can show you here ..."},{"time":461660,"text":"There is the statue from Hatra"},{"time":464598,"text":"and the Lion of Mosul."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466442,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473870,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475044,"text":"Now, if you look closely,"},{"time":476572,"text":"you'll notice that there are some parts\nthat have been printed in color,"},{"time":481103,"text":"and some parts that are in white or gray."},{"time":484715,"text":"This part was added\nsimply to hold the statues up."},{"time":488834,"text":"This works the same way\nif you visit a museum,"},{"time":491285,"text":"and a statue is found in fragments;"},{"time":493590,"text":"it's put together\nfor the people to see it."},{"time":495884,"text":"This makes sense, right?"},{"time":498521,"text":"However, we're much more interested"},{"time":500298,"text":"in what virtual reality\nhas to offer for lost heritage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504420,"text":"Here is an example\nof one of the tower tombs"},{"time":506945,"text":"that was destroyed in Palmyra."},{"time":508844,"text":"Using Sketchfab's online viewer,"},{"time":510822,"text":"we can show that we have reconstructed\nthree parts of the exterior of the tomb,"},{"time":516501,"text":"but we also have photos of the inside,"},{"time":518430,"text":"so we're beginning to create\na reconstruction of the wall"},{"time":521123,"text":"and the ceiling."},{"time":522781,"text":"Archaeologists worked there\nfor many, many years,"},{"time":525712,"text":"so we also have architectural\ndrawing plans of this lost heritage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532339,"text":"Unfortunately, we are not only losing\ncultural heritage to areas of conflict"},{"time":538745,"text":"and at war --"},{"time":539920,"text":"we're also losing it to natural disasters."},{"time":542878,"text":"This is a 3D model\nof Durbar Square in Kathmandu,"},{"time":546772,"text":"before the earthquake\nthat occurred last April ..."},{"time":550297,"text":"and this is after."},{"time":552563,"text":"You may be thinking,"},{"time":554185,"text":"you didn't create these 3D models\nwith only tourist photographs,"},{"time":557878,"text":"and that's true."},{"time":559293,"text":"But what this represents"},{"time":560793,"text":"is the ability for large, public\norganizations and private industry"},{"time":564563,"text":"to come together\nfor initiatives like ours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569759,"text":"And so one of the major challenges\nof our project, really,"},{"time":572871,"text":"is to find photographs that were taken\nbefore something happens, right?"},{"time":577620,"text":"Well, the internet is basically a database\nwith millions of images, right?"},{"time":583668,"text":"Exactly."},{"time":585043,"text":"So we have begun to develop a tool"},{"time":588502,"text":"that allows us to extract images\nfrom websites like Flickr,"},{"time":592448,"text":"based on their geotags,"},{"time":593970,"text":"to complete reconstructions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596396,"text":"Because we're not only losing cultural\nheritage to natural disasters and in war,"},{"time":603183,"text":"but we're also losing it\nto something else."},{"time":607777,"text":"Any idea, just looking\nat these two pictures?"},{"time":611649,"text":"Maybe it's a little difficult to remember,"},{"time":614313,"text":"but only a few weeks ago,"},{"time":616757,"text":"this was the example of human\ndestruction by human stupidity."},{"time":621949,"text":"Because a tourist in Lisbon\nwanted to climb onto this statue"},{"time":627282,"text":"and take a selfie with it --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628671,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629696,"text":"and pulled it down with him."},{"time":631596,"text":"So we're already finding photographs"},{"time":633609,"text":"to complete a digital\nreconstruction of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636974,"text":"We need to remember"},{"time":638284,"text":"that the destruction of cultural heritage\nisn't a recent phenomenon."},{"time":643664,"text":"In the 16th century,"},{"time":645006,"text":"European priests and explorers burned\nthousands of Maya books in the Americas,"},{"time":651508,"text":"of which we only have a handful left."},{"time":655444,"text":"Fast-forward to 2001,"},{"time":657199,"text":"when the Taliban blew up\nthe Bamiyan Buddhas in Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661754,"text":"You see,"},{"time":663513,"text":"cultural heritage\nis about our shared global history."},{"time":668820,"text":"It helps us connect\nwith our ancestors and their stories,"},{"time":672585,"text":"but we're losing pieces of it\nevery day to natural disasters"},{"time":676880,"text":"and in areas of conflict."},{"time":680114,"text":"Of course, the loss of human life\nis the most heartbreaking loss ..."},{"time":685742,"text":"but cultural heritage offers us a way\nto preserve the memory of the people"},{"time":691602,"text":"for future generations."},{"time":694329,"text":"We need your help to reclaim\nthe history that is being lost."},{"time":699352,"text":"Will you join us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":701399,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}